				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what is a mandolin good for<a name="22869"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 04 11:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mandolin boosts the gain from your regen songs and the dmg from, some, of your dots.
<br />

<br />
IE. Hymn of Restoration uses String skill, and Chords of Dissonance uses String skill.
<br />

<br />
In the example of the Hymn of Restoration...
<br />

<br />
Your song will regenerate a set amount of HP back each tick (every 6 seconds) that it is displayed in your Song-buffs window.
<br />

<br />
Hymn of Restoration	
<br />

<br />
HP by 2(L6) to 14(L65); 	Group Buff	Stringed
<br />

<br />
This means, at level 6 (L6) your song will regen 2 hp per tick while you sing it. However, with a mandolin...
<br />

<br />
Mandolin  	 Mod: 2.0 	 Wts: 0.0 	 Stringed
<br />

<br />
Mandolin (and Lute too for that matter) has a Modifier of 2.0.
<br />
This means your song, while using the Mandolin, will do...
<br />

<br />
2 hp/tick x 2.0 (modifier for Mandolin) = 4 hp/tick.
<br />

<br />
Or at L65, it would do 14 hp/tick x 2.0 = 28 hp/tick.
<br />

<br />
Look at the Instruments and the Song sections of eqdiva.com. All modifiers and the song info is listed there. &quot;)
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
